snippet.textDisplay: I feel like this situation isn't as black and white as people are making it seem. I fully understand the idea of them having the free will to make the decision to step down from being royals, but I'm not entirely sold on the fact that they've actually planned this properly. I mean the royal family's wealth is based on taxpayer's money; if Harry and Meghan step down who is (at least initially) funding it? Even their home in Windsor cost approximately £2.4 million to refurbish, are they still entitled to these possessions that were paid for with the public's money; the same public that they'll no longer entirely fulfill their responsibilities for. Truly and honestly if they wish to step down that's their choice, I can't have an opinion on that, but not consulting the royal family in detail about their plan is dismissing protocol and, in some ways, damaging the united front the British public expect the royal family to represent the country with. If they have planned this thoroughly then, by all means, they can do what they want. Yet, the fact that this has left Buckingham Palace in a stir and that the most we've got is an Instagram post kind of suggests that they've jumped the gun here... Sorry for the rant, I really didn't realise how much I had to say till it was said
